I super hate the planeswalker decks and I don’t think I knew exactly why until just recently. 

I understand they’re an effective and splashy tool to entice and teach new players. That’s legit. I share a bit of prof’s gripe about how these cards are specifically designed to be undesirable for experienced players (aka they’re bad) and when a new player gets good enough it kinda sucks to find out your cards suck. Not only that, they suck on purpose. That’s tough. 

But that’s not even my big gripe with them. I dislike extra-standard material. Commander cards and conspiracy are playable in both Commander and legacy, those are fine. But Standard is supposed to be a more sacred cow. Only one pathway into the format. Random extra stuff is precisely that: extra. 

And it wouldn’t really be an issue except they hold Modern to that same obligation. They won’t create new modern-legal cards in a supplemental product, they have to filter through standard. Which means Modern is the only format they don’t design extra cards for. Why is Modern more untouchable than standard? I just want a consistent rule, wotc!
